Basic steps:
`sudo ufw default deny incoming` - deny all incoming requests by default:
`sudo ufw allow from <IP_ADDRESS>` - do this for known validator IPs. You can find these on taostats under the axon column: https://taostats.io/subnets/72/metagraph?order=stake%3Adesc
`sudo ufw allow ssh`- allow ssh requests from any IP (so you don't lock yourself out if you connect to your machine with a dynamic IP address.

Now, this could have some side affects. For example, if a trusted validator changes their IP, or they route egress through a proxy, your firewall may reject legitimate traffic. We are working on a more permanent solution, but this is my suggestion if you are experiencing these issues.
